Second session today was a skill focused two-piece workout. A) AMRAP 20 of 2 RMU and 6 dumbbell OHS (30kg/70lbs) B) 3 RFQ of 15 alt. dumbbell snatch (30kg/70lbs) with switch in the ground.  The A-piece would've been conditioning work if RMU's weren't such a skill/strength bottleneck and the OHS had been a bit lighter. I managed 12 rounds+2 RMU (26 RMU and 72 OHS) while only pushing my rest times in the last 5 minutes. Obviously still a glaring weakness, but I made some good technique improvements. I found a much tighter spot to hit in my kip that made the turnover much faster.  #crossfit #cf #tr√¶ning #training #fitness #workout #wod #muscleup #rings #skillwork #skill #gymnastics #dumbbell #s√∏ndermarken #valby #kbh #frb #cph #homegym #hjemmetr√¶ning #stronghealth #roguefitness @stronghealthfitness #udend√∏rs #outdoortraininh #manwithaplan #week17 #day5 #beAwesome

At Impact Roasters, we believe that it is important to invest in job creation projects for the youth that resides in the areas where our coffee comes from. One of the projects that we have carried out through our nonprofit organization called Coffeeprint4Change is a concrete block production facility that employs local young men and women committed to being part of our aim to change and shape the local community. Valby station replaced the first station (1847-1864) in 1911. From 1934 also for s-trains. A temporary station served until 1941. The station was enlarged 1953 to the west and is in the top 10 of Denmarks most used stations  #Valby #station #railroad #denmark #copenhagen #cph #trainstation #visitcopenhagen #rushhour #myldretid #stog #bahnhof #danskerneshistorie

J. C. Jacobsen (1811-1887) Founder of world famous Carlsberg Breweries, named after his son, Carl and the hill (bjerg or berg) near the then small village Valby. Like the editors of Politivennen, Jacobsen was captain of the Copenhagen civil militsia, Borgerv√¶bningen, and minded for the bourgeois society. His relations to his son Carl (1842-1914), founder of Ny Carlsberg, 1871 deteriorated over the years, They never reconciled. #carlsberg #statue #vesterbro #copenhagen #k√∏benhavn #cph #canonphotography #nofilter #udenfilter #oplevdanmark #visitcopenhagen #visitdenmark #delditk√∏benhavn @carlsberg @carlsbergbyen #valby #danskerneshistorie

Goodmorning everyone!  Ever heard of camu camu? Most people haven't, but actually this little cherry sized berry grows in the Amazon region in South America and is known to be rich in C-vitamin and in some cases has been measured to have 60-times more than a regular orange! Quite fascinating  The taste could remind us of acidic fruits like lime or lemon. Now that phase 1 of our remodel is coming to a close, we have the pleasure of putting up art pieces and making this house more of a home. A precious heirloom from my Grandma Weesie now hangs in the entryway- each woman represents the clothing worn from different Danish islands and regions. Reading about each area and the people that come from there fills my heart with an indescribable feeling of love, respect, and honor to be another link in the chain of that rich Danish blood. I am so grateful for my ancestors and the beautiful, artistic, humble example of one of the most influential people in my life, my "maga". This week's commute - through Carlsberg.  Carlsberg City District is a small area in Vesterbro in Copenhagen, bordering to the Frederiksberg and Valby districts. The area is named after Carlsberg's beer, which was brewed on the premises from 1847 - 2008. However the visitor centre Visit Carlsberg and Jacobsen House Brewery, which produces special brews, are still located here.  The Carlsberg grounds are currently being transformed into a new neighbourhood called Carlsberg City District and is welcoming new tennants like educational instiutions, shops, caf√©s and its very own S-train station: Carlsberg Station. #commute #workingmummy #joinery #carpentry #buildingsite #Carlsberg #visitcarlsberg #newtown #city #development #architecture #mordern #history #beer #brewery #vesterbro #frederiksberg #s√∏ndermarken #valby #copenhagen

Today is Limu coffee beans day at our roastery.  Limu is a high-quality washed Ethiopian coffee bean grown at elevations ranging from 1,800 to 2,100 meters in the southwest region. Nordic Hamstring Ô∏èHaseskader er en skade der ofte foreg√•r i sportsgrene med h√∏j fart, enten i en sprint eller ved et strakt ben. Netop fordi haseskader ofte skader i yderbanen, er Nordic Hamstring √∏velsen en af de store skadesreducerende √∏velser for hasemuskulaturen da den tr√¶ner muskulaturen eksentriske kraft. ---------------------------------------------------Blandt andet har et dansk studie blandt 942 fodboldspillere vist at √∏velsen reducerede haseskader med 70%, og 85% hos dem der tidligere havde haft en hase skade. Det er enorme resultater.  Forslag til protokoller  van der Horst N, et al. Am J Sports Med. 2015. Hotel & Restaurant Fy & Bi, Valby. Halloween is an ancient celtic tradition (Samhain) to celebrate witches, ghosts and the dark powers. Christianity (catholicism) tried to it take over, and called it Allehelgensaften, All Saints Evening. Protestants disliked catholic traditions, so in 1770, it was abolished. But since 2000 the celtic tradition has been transformed and returned from the USA, and orange pumpkins with lights inside can be seen everywhere. Valby Skole 1917, architect Hans Peter Jacobsen (1877-1943). Any passenger passing Valby by train must admire these beautiful old industrial buildings, now housing Valby Skole. They were built for Porcel√¶nsfabrikken Norden (now Royal Copenhagen). The factory produced high resistant porcelain, able to resist 2 million Volt. When it closed in the 1980s, the school moved in.  #ValbySkole #Valby #Porcel√¶nsfabrikken #HansPeterJacobsen #arkitektur #architecture #architecturelovers #danskerneshistorie #k√∏benhavn #copenhagen #aokdk #visitcopenhagen #igerscopenhagen #cphpicks #mitkbh  #nofilter #udenfilter #loves_united_copenhagen #tipkbh

üá©üá∞ Name: Jacobsen Porter __________ Brauerei: Husbryggeriet Jacobsen (Carlsberg-Gruppe), #Kopenhagen, #D√§nemark __________ Beschreibung (offiziell): Jacobsen Porter is a traditional top-fermented porter with depth in both taste and aroma. Jacobsen Golden Naked Christmas Ale.  Clear, copper colored beer with a three finger high, creamy head that leaves lacing on the glass.  Nose: Caramel malt, fudge, dried fruit and butter.  Taste: Roasted malt, burned sugar, red berries, anise, brown sugar, raisin, alcohol, cinnamon and orange peel.  Mouth: Medium body and high carbonation. Light bitter the end.  My rating: 3.1 of 5. Kjeldsg√•rdsvej 35 (1918). Two examples of early urbanization in Valby. Pilestykket, Husvildebarakker,  1947. 72 barracks, designed by architect Frederik Christian Lund (1896-1984). Functionalism. They were made in Sweden, still painted ‚ÄúSwedish Red‚Äù, and made for German refugees from refugee camp Kl√∏vermarkslejren. When they returned to Germany, the barracks were used for homeless. It was meant as a temporary solution, but later facilities were added and they still exist for permanent use. The lampposts in the background is the stadion Valby Idr√¶tspark. The smoke: Aved√∏rev√¶rket.  #Valby #husvildebarakker #barracks #funktionalisme #functionalism #FrederikChristianLund #FCLund #arkitektur #architecture #architecturelovers #bygningskultur #bygningshistorie #danskerneshistorie #k√∏benhavn #copenhagen #aokdk #visitcopenhagen #igerscopenhagen #cphpicks #mitkbh #canonphotography #nofilter #udenfilter #archi_focus_on #frostvejr #frostweather

Christmas Basket - Ethiopian Coffee Body Scrub --------------------------------- The body scrub was developed by Impact Roasters team, and its inspiration stems from our aspiration for a more sustainable way of living.  The coffee grounds used as a base for the body scrub is a waste product, and we decided to put it to good use.  With a base of almond oil, coconut sugar, cinnamon and scented with peppermint essential oil the body scrub is to exfoliate, moisturize and antioxidize your skin.  The Ethiopian coffee body scrub is part of our Christmas Basket, but it can also be purchased separately at our roastery and coffee shop at Langgade st. . . . . . #impactroasters #impacttrade #impact #christmasbasket #christmasgift #julegaver #bodyscrub #coffeebodyscrub #sustainableproducts #handmade #h√•ndlavet #ethiopiskkaffe #ethiopiancoffee #roaster #coffeeroastery #specialtycoffee #sustainablecoffee #danmark #delditkbh #kaffe #mitvalby #valby #valbylanggade #singleorigin #specialtycoffee #sidama #yirgacheffe #limu

Trekroner Bryggeri. The factory was established 1899, and was meant to house the brewery from 1899, designed by Caspar Leuning Borch. Only one third of the brewery is left. A war broke out between Carlsberg and De forenede Bryggerier, the latter swallowing up the brewery even before it moved in. The last beer left the factory in 1915, and was used by the tannery Ballin & Hertz. ‚ÄúSpinderiet‚Äù, Valby. The cotton factory (left) was build 1907 and closed by the end of the 1950s. It had its own nursery, Spindeg√•rden 1948-1965. Typical textile industry building with many and large windows to bring light inside. Then local crafters and industries moved in, until a shopping center was designed with old and new buildings 2007. Unlike many other shopping centers, is partly outdoor with a glass roof. Legendary union boss (SiD), Hardy Hansen (b. 1933) worked here for a short time until 1954. #spinderiet #valby #arkitektur #architecture #architecturelovers #total_denmark  #k√∏benhavn #copenhagen #danskerneshistorie#k√∏benhavn #copenhagen #aokdk #visitcopenhagen #igerscopenhagen #cphpicks #mitkbh  #nofilter #udenfilter #loves_united_copenhagen #tipkbh

Valby Station, early morning. This is where most of my hikes start - and end. The station is the second (1911), the first existed 1847-1864. Tracks for international, national, local and metropolitan lines, the latter shown on the photo, from 1934. In 1950-1953 the station expanded. Do I need to mention that the architect was Heinrich Wenck, my honoured followers? Tonite is showdown for 2017. Happy New Year! We are so glad about our coffee tree, which is around 20 years old and makes our roastery and coffee shop way more beautiful.  We just saw that coffee cherries have started to ripen slowly. Jesuskirken (1891, the separate tower, 1895). There are many photos of this church, this angle is scarcely used because it is only possible on a clear winter‚Äôs days. Designed by Vilhelm Dahlerup, financed by brewer Jacobsen, and inspired by ancient Italian cathedrals. The church got quite a few unusual decorations, like pentagrams, Zodiac symbols, and unlike most Danish churches, it is directed north-south (usually east-west). #Valby #Jesuskirken #church #kirke #arkitektur #architecture #architecturelovers #bygningskultur #bygningshistorie #danskerneshistorie #total_denmark #igersdenmark #k√∏benhavn #copenhagen #aokdk #visitcopenhagen #visitdenmark #igerscopenhagen #cphpicks #mitkbh #canonphotography #nofilter #udenfilter  #citylife #loves_united_copenhagen @CopenhagenHeat #tipkbh #myplanet_facades #archi_focus_on #voreskbh) #vilhelmdahlerup
